How to build/run:
-- Tested with ruby 1.9.3p194
1) install opencv via packagemanager or manually
2) ruby manually or via. rvm(ruby version manager - preferred method)
3) install ruby gems and bundler
4) install gems needed to run program with command: bundle install
   this will install the needed gem (opencv) listed in the Gemfile
5) run houghlines.rb/houghcircles.rb with: ruby houghlines.rb <image | houghlines file> <0=normal houghlines algorithm| 1=probabilistic houghlines mode>
   detailed help: run houghlines/houghcircles without arguments

